s%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20list%20of%20places%20you're%20targeting%2C%20you%20can%20%E2%80%94%20and%20should%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-says-this-best-way-to-find-job-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enetwork%20before%20the%20job%20gets%20posted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20veteran%20career%20coach%20Laura%20Labovich%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20That's%20because%20once%20a%20job%20listing%20is%20live%2C%20recruiters%20and%20hiring%20managers%20aren't%20likely%20to%20do%20more%20than%20point%20you%20to%20the%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249aaf019-2a6d-4221-a3be-813cedc4b30b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClimb%20the%20corporate%20ladder%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20ladder%2C%20you%20can%20only%20go%20up%20or%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20scaling%20a%20corporate%20hierarchy%20has%20become%20outdated%20for%20many%20workers%2C%20Christian%20Tr%C3%B6ster%2C%20an%20Academy%20of%20Management%20scholar%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20leadership%20and%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20Germany's%20K%C3%BChne%20Logistics%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20he%20said%2C%20people%20might%20want%20to%20consider%20what%20he%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bprotean%26quot%3B%20career%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20changes%20shape%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETr%C3%B6ster%20said%20that%20rather%20than%20ascending%20a%20ladder%2C%20a%20better%20aim%20for%20many%20workers%20would%20be%20to%20become%20%26quot%3Bpsychologically%20successful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ultimate%20goal%20of%20your%20career%20is%20feeling%20proud%20and%20accomplished%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20practical%20reason%20you%20might%20not%20want%20to%20climb%20the%20ladder%20is%20that%20a%20push%20by%20some%20corporate%20leaders%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-amazon-google-embrace-flatter-stru