a%20brief%20break%20from%20the%20company%20to%20work%20for%20a%20startup%20in%20Palo%20Alto.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-work-after-maternity-leave-google-ai-engineer-tech-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereturned%20to%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%202009%20and%20spent%20time%20on%20several%20teams%2C%20including%20Google%20Maps%2C%20emerging%20markets%2C%20and%20corporate%20engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20I%20asked%20a%20colleague%20who'd%20recently%20moved%20to%20a%20new%20team%20what%20she%20was%20working%20on%2C%20but%20she%20said%20she%20couldn't%20really%20talk%20about%20it.%20It%20was%20really%20unusual%20for%20people%20to%20be%20tight-lipped%20about%20their%20work%2C%20so%20I%20was%20curious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f8552b8-01a7-4adf-8602-f3601fb5fe35%5C%22%3EI%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20I%20was%20walking%20into%2C%20but%20Google%20Duplex%20blew%20me%20away%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spoke%20to%20her%20manager%2C%20who%20showed%20me%20an%20early%20demo%20of%20the%20project%2C%20which%20was%20called%20Blue%20Ginger%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-duplex-will-identify-itself-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eit%20became%20Google%20Duplex%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20AI%20calling%20up%20a%20restaurant%20and%20booking%20a%20reservation.%20Even%20at%20that%20early%20stage%2C%20the%20voice%20sounded%20so%20real%20that%20it%20reminded%20me%20of%20the%20movie%20%26quot%3BHer.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20blown%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20join%20the%20team.%20They%20were%20only%20accepting%20internal%20transfers%20at%20that%20point%3A%20they%20had%20to%20know%20who%20you%20were%20and%20what%20you'd%20done.%20A%20part%20of%20me%20really%20liked%20that%20exclusivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20bunch%20of%20conversations%20with%20the%20team%20manager%20so%20he%20could%20decide%20if%20I%20was%20a%20good%20match.%20I%20highlighted%20my%20previous%20career%20accomplishments%20and%20ability%20to%20quickly%20contribute%20ideas.%20I%20can%20only%20speculate%2C%20but%20I'd%20say%20he%20chose%20me%20for%20a%20combination%20of%20my%20communication%20skills%20and%20my%20track%20record%20at%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20I'd%20launched%20other%20products%20in%20the%20past%2C%20which%20probably%20helped%20establish%20my%20credibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e80f09c5-5bfc-44b6-95d4-92cae16b15d8%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20retool%20myself%20to%20work%20on%20an%20AI-focused%20team%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-amazon-management-leadership-advice-how-to-run-business%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emanaging%20a%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20working%20on%20a%20visual%20interface%20to%20help%20human%20operators%20assess%20and%20correct%20how%20the%20Duplex%20AI%20system%20interpreted%20phone%20conversations%2C%20to%20improve%20the%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20been%20exposed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmachine-learning-engineer-amazon-career-change-software-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emachine%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20AI%20concepts%20on%20my%20previous%20teams%20at%20Google%2C%20but%20I'd%20never%20been%20on%20one%20actively%20building%20models%20and%20doing%20core%20data%20science%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20brought%20my%20experience%20building%20software%20and%20managing%20people%20to%20the%20team%2C%20and%20while%20some%20members%20had%20more%20expertise%20in%20AI%2C%20most%20of%20us%20had%20to%20retool%20ourselves%20to%20learn%20this%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20set%20up%20long%20discussions%20with%20others%20on%20the%20team%20who%20could%20explain%20how%20the%20system%20worked%2C%20but%20I%20wish%20I'd%20spent%20more%20time%20meeting%20with%20the%20other%20AI%20teams%20at%20Google%2C%20to%20get%20a%20feel%20for%20how%20they%20applied%20AI%20and%20machine%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20big%20companies%2C%20there%20are%20teams%20of%20extraordinary%20people%20all%20over%20the%20place.%20If%20I'd%20taken%20advantage%20of%20that%20environment%20more%2C%20I%20could%20have%20met%20with%20people%20who%20formed%20Google%20Brain%20or%20DeepMind%20and%20learned%20from%20them%20while%20we%20were%20at%20the%20same%20company%20and%20were%20able%20to%20be%20more%20open%20with%20me%20about%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Patrick%20Leung%20sitting%20in%20a%20Google%20office.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68ee54275dbc4fd10daacbf5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPatrick%20Leung%20joined%20Google%20in%202007%20and%20pivoted%20onto%20an%20AI%20team%20in%202017.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Patrick%20Leung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273d30e38-2fc3-4233-b705-c1abd2575aae%5C%22%3EWhen%20we%20launched%20Google%20Duplex%2C%20we%20knew%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20big%20deal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20lead-up%20to%20the%20launch%2C%20we%20wondered%20how%20the%20product%20would%20be%20received%20because%20of%20growing%20caution%20about%20AI%20taking%20people's%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20media%20frenzy%20when%20it%20launched%20in%202018.%20Some%20people%20thought%20it%20was%20unethical%2C%20and%20others%20thought%20it%20might%20be%20fake.%20Stephen%20Colbert%20even%20did%20a%20satirical%20skit%20about%20us.%20It%20was%20a%20privilege%20to%20be%20part%20of%20a%20launch%20that%20touched%20the%20zeitgeist%20of%20popular%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2010%20years%20with%20Google%2C%20the%20time%20came%20to%20move%20on.%20In%202019%2C%20I%20joined%20a%20financial%20sciences%20company%20as%20their%20CTO%20for%20private%20investments.%20Currently%2C%20I'm%20a%20CTO%20at%20a%20company%20called%20Faro%20Health%2C%20where%20I'm%20using%20AI%20to%20improve%20clinical%20drug%20trials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d64331fd-1739-4271-9ef9-548ce074df42%5C%22%3EMy%20top%20tip%20for%20breaking%20into%20AI%20is%20to%20build%20up%20real-world%20experience.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20possible%20in%20your%20current%20job%2C%20seek%20out%20opportunities%20to%20apply%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flimits-large-language-models-chatgpt-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-openai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elarge%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20real%20business%20problem.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20mine%20with%20no%20coding%20experience%20used%20AI%20to%20personalize%20outreach%20messages%20while%20recruiting%20for%20clinical%20positions%2C%20which%20improved%20her%20response%20rates.%20If%20there%20aren't%20opportunities%20like%20this%20at%20work%2C%20do%20it%20in%20your%20spare%20time%20and%20put%20it%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20looking%20to%20work%20in%20a%20certain%20area%2C%20it%20would%20probably%20help%20if%20you%20built%20a%20system%20that%20was%20directly%20applicable%20to%20it%2C%20but%20it%20could%20even%20just%20be%20something%20you're%20interested%20in%2C%20like%20summarizing%20movie%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20barrier%20to%20getting%20involved%20in%20this%20field%20is%20lower%20than%20it's%20ever%20been.%20You%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20train%20your%20own%20model%3B%20you%20can%20just%20start%20talking%20to%20the%20large%20language%20model%20and%20do%20interesting%20things.%20You%20don't%20need%20to%20be%20an%20expert%20in%20machine%20learning%20to%20make%20things%20happen.%20Even%20coding%20is%20becoming%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-limits-learn-to-code-engineers-openai-microsoft-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautomated%20thanks%20to%20vibe%20coding.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20demonstrate%20that%20they%20can%20wield%20LLMs%20effectively%20are%20going%20to%20find%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%