elected%20to%20take%20a%20nationwide%20test%20%E2%80%94%20commonly%20known%20as%20the%20Nation's%20Report%20Card%20%E2%80%94%20that%20compares%20achievement%20across%20all%20states%2C%20helping%20policymakers%20and%20teachers%20determine%20necessary%20interventions%20at%20the%20local%20and%20federal%20levels%2C%20so%20students%20like%20Jack%20have%20the%20best%20tools%20to%20help%20them%20keep%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20Education%20Department's%20research%20arm%2C%20tracking%20Jack's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-alpha-reading-literacy-crisis-privilege-society-divide-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprogress%20in%20math%20and%20reading%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20become%20a%20lot%20more%20difficult.%20That%20makes%20the%20department's%20%24900%20million%20cut%20to%20research%20contracts%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20top%20of%20my%20list%20of%20things%20to%20worry%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Margaret%20Spellings%2C%20the%20education%20secretary%20for%20former%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush.%20Spellings%20tells%20me%20that%20without%20the%20grants%2C%20it's%20unclear%20how%20states%20and%20districts%20will%20get%20the%20data%20they%20need%20to%20best%20help%20their%20students%20succeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20provides%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20and%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20that%20guide%20policymakers%20at%20the%20federal%20and%20state%2C%20and%20local%20levels%20about%20how%20we're%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Spellings%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20shows%20us%20who's%20doing%20well%20and%20who's%20not%20doing%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20the%20National%20Assessment%20Governing%20Board%20voted%20to%20cut%20some%20assessments%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20with%20the%20intent%20to%20save%20money%2C%20including%20the%20state-level%20math%20and%20reading%20tests%20for%2012th%20graders%20and%20performance%20tracking%20in%20urban%20school%20districts.%20Specifically%2C%20the%20cuts%20mean%20that%20fourth%20graders%2C%20who%20were%20supposed%20to%20take%20a%20science%20assessment%20in%202028%20and%202032%2C%20won't%20be%20taking%20that%20first%20test%2C%20and%20the%20writing%20test%20for%20fourth%2C%20eighth%2C%20and%2012th%20graders%20in%202032%20was%20canceled%20altogether%2C%20stripping%20school%20districts%20of%20those%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPotter%20says%20the%20potential%20loss%20of%20valuable%20information%20has%20already%20created%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20instability%26quot%3B%20across%20public%20schools%20that%20have%20historically%20used%20that%20data%20to%20assess%20progress%20over%20time.%20She%20adds%20that%20some%20magnet%20schools%20use%20the%20data%20to%20apply%20for%20and%20receive%20federal%20grants%2C%20and%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20that%20grant%20process%20will%20continue%20after%20the%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOngoing%20cuts%20can%20directly%20harm%20students%20like%20Jack.%20The%20Institute%20of%20Education%20Sciences%2C%20the%20nonpartisan%20research%20arm%20of%20the%20Education%20Department%2C%20uses%20classrooms%20across%20the%20country%20as%20data%20points%20in%20its%20research.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20might%20provide%20technology%20to%20classrooms%20and%20assess%20how%20students%20are%20learning%20using%20that%20technology%20to%20determine%20whether%20it%20helps%20them%20progress.%20Cuts%20to%20that%20research%20mean%20Jack%20may%20no%20longer%20be%20able%20to%20use%20the%20computer%20system%20that%20was%20helping%20him%20advance%20in%20math.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeverson%20said%20the%20uncertainty%20makes%20her%20feel%20%26quot%3Bhelpless.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20in%20a%20spot%20where%20my%20hands%20are%20tied%2C%20and%20I%20just%20wish%20there%20was%20more%20I%20could%20do%20for%20my%20students%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20can't%2C%20with%20what's%20going%20on%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20can't%20protect%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcMahon%20wrote%20in%20congressional%20testimony%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bbegan%20this%20year%20by%20canceling%20and%20renegotiating%20a%20number%20of%20contracts%2C%20and%20we%20are%20now%20redirecting%20those%20resources%20toward%20a%20leaner%20operation%20that%20will%20provide%20useful%20data%20and%20tools%20for%20teachers%2C%20education%20experts%2C%20and%20school%20administrators.%26quot%3B%20Despite%20the%20assurances%2C%20the%20department%20hasn't%20indicated%20plans%20to%20outsource%20data%20collection%20to%20another%20agency%2C%20and%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20it%20plans%20to%20bolster%20those%20efforts%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20conversation%20hosted%20by%20The%20Federalist%20Society%20on%20September%2017%2C%20McMahon%20said%20that%20she%20is%20%26quot%3Bwinding%20down%26quot%3B%20the%20department's%20activities%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20give%20more%20power%20to%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20trying%20to%20do%20is%20to%20show%20how%20we%20can%20move%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20to%20show%20that%20they%20can%20be%20more%20efficiently%20operating%20in%20other%20agencies%2C%26quot%3B%20McMahon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMadi%20Biedermann%2C%20deputy%20assistant%20secretary%20for%20communications%20at%20the%20department%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20department%20looks%20%26quot%3Bforward%20to%20identifying%20additional%20strategies%20to%20make%20education%20programs%20more%20efficient%20and%20effective%20for%20students%2C%20families%2C%20and%20taxpayers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205967d15-2bcf-4ac5-bf00-cb1f32094e62%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStudent-loan%20repayment%20and%20forgiveness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EK-12%20funding%20is%20just%20one%20bucket%20that%20the%20department%20facilitates%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20also%20responsible%20for%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20flowing%20through%20the%20country's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-back-on-ibr-borrowers-debt-relief-processing-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigher%20education%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Proposed%20changes%20or%20cuts%20to%20the%20vast%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmajor-student-loan-debt-repayment-changes-trump-kicks-off-negotiations-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estudent-loan%20repayment%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20our%20hypothetical%20teacher%2C%20Ms.%20Smith%2C%20at%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-plan-blocked-student-loan-borrowers-fear-higher-payments-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigher%20monthly%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20loan%20forgiveness%20on%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Fast%2C%20The%20Century%20Foundation's%20director%20of%20higher%20education%20policy%2C%20says%20staffing%20cuts%20at%20the%20agency%20and%20the%20fallout%20from%20the%20One%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%20Act%2C%20which%20was%20signed%20into%20law%20in%20July%2C%20will%20complicate%20the%20already%20complex%20student-loan%20system.%20The%20OBBB%20eliminated%20existing%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%20and%20replaced%20them%20with%20two%20less%20generous%20options%2C%20meaning%20borrowers%20will%20face%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-major-repayment-overhaul-big-beautiful-bill-trump-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eharder%20time%20achieving%20debt%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20staffing%20cuts%20at%20the%20Education%20Department%20mean%20borrowers%20seeking%20help%20with%20repayment%20or%20with%20their%20servicers%20are%20likelier%20to%20see%20their%20phone%20calls%20go%20unanswered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20dismantling%20of%20the%20department%20will%20have%20the%20most%20immediate%20and%20soonest%20effect%20on%20people's%20day-to-day%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Fast%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20that'll%20show%20up%20is%20just%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20are%20frustrated%20and%20unable%20to%20get%20help%20with%20problems%20that%20they're%20having%20with%20their%20loan%20repayment%2C%20or%20potentially%20with%20their%20financial%20aid%20to%20go%20to%20school.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20spending%20law%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-borrowing-caps-professional-degrees-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eplaces%20new%20borrowing%20caps%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20graduate%20and%20professional%20students%2C%20which%20will%20cut%20some%20borrowers%20off%20from%20pursuing%20a%20medical%20or%20law%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20or%20push%20them%20toward%20the%20riskier%20private%20student-loan%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20district%20that's%20already%20short%20on%20money%2C%20Stambaugh%20says%20that%20should%20federal%20funds%20stop%20flowing%2C%20her%20school%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20slack%2C%20and%20students%20will%20suffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20potentially%20very%2C%20very%20devastating%20and%20starts%20to%20feel%20very%20much%20like%20we're%20under%20attack%20for%20just%20trying%20to%20do%20something%20that%20makes%20the%20world%20a%20better%20place%2C%20makes%20kids'%20lives%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d698f077-66ae-43e0-8f9e-adf1f4a15fab%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Blow%20it%20up%20and%20rebuild'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20is%20not%20flawless.%20Beth%20Akers%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20conservative%20think%20tank%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20says%20there%20is%20room%20for%20%26quot%3Bsome%20significant%20reform%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20agency's%20practices%20but%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20may%20be%20taking%20its%20push%20too%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20comes%20back%20to%20this%20philosophy%20that%20this%20administration%20seems%20to%20be%20holding%2C%20which%20is%20that%20yes%2C%20we%20see%20that%20there's%20these%20problems.%20We%20see%20there's%20significant%20need%20for%20reform.%20We've%20also%20seen%20previous%20administrations%20fail%20to%20make%20the%20sort%20of%20normal-looking%20reforms%20that%20people%20would%20expect.%20So%20we're%20going%20to%20blow%20it%20up%20and%20rebuild%2C%26quot%3B%20Akers%20tells%20me.%20But%20this%20aggressive%20approach%2C%20abruptly%20firing%20staff%20and%20cutting%20funding%2C%20probably%20isn't%20the%20way%20she%20would%20go%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Huffman%2C%20a%20former%20commissioner%20for%20Tennessee's%20education%20department%20who%20worked%20for%20a%20Republican%20governor%2C%20says%20that%20while%20he's%20%26quot%3Bsympathetic%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20we%20want%20less%20bureaucracy%2C%26quot%3B%20that's%20not%20a%20reason%20to%20ax%20the%20federal%20agency.%20Eliminating%20the%20Education%20Department%2C%20he%20says%2C%20would%20run%20counter%20to%20Trump's%20goal%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffive-years-student-debt-relief-suddenly-over-trump-default-collections-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereducing%20waste%20and%20boosting%20efficiency%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Trump's%20plan%20involves%20redirecting%20the%20department's%20responsibilities%20to%20other%20agencies%2C%20but%20having%20a%20centralized%20department%20to%20track%20and%20distribute%20funds%20to%20schools%2C%20colleges%2C%20and%20education%20researchers%20makes%20it%20less%20likely%20that%20the%20cash%20goes%20to%20waste%20or%20that%20efforts%20are%20duplicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%20the%20Education%20Department's%20responsibilities%20would%20be%20split%20up.%20Trump%20has%20suggested%20that%20the%20federal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffired-federal-workers-risk-losing-pslf-student-loan-forgiveness-rifs-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estudent-loan%20portfolio%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20transferred%20to%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%2C%20and%20special-needs%20programs%20would%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services.%20Recent%20court%20documents%20disclosed%20that%20the%20department%20was%20already%20looking%20into%20transferring%20some%20financial%20aid%20responsibilities%20to%20the%20Treasury%20Department.%20Jonathan%20Zimmerman%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20education%20history%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20says%20the%20uncertainty%20means%20there's%20the%20risk%20that%20students%20who%20rely%20on%20funding%20from%20the%20department%20%26quot%3Bwill%20get%20lost%20in%20the%20shuffle%2C%20and%20that%20the%20parts%20of%20the%20Education%20Department%20that%20are%20devoted%20to%20them%20won't%20actually%20be%20replaced%20elsewhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20from%20a%20state%20education%20chief's%20perspective%2C%20regardless%20of%20political%20affiliation%2C%20Huffman%20says%20spreading%20out%20the%20Education%20Department's%20responsibilities%20would%20just%20make%20things%20a%20lot%20more%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20call%20the%20people%20I%20knew%20at%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Education%20and%20get%20answers%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20we%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20of%20having%20to%20do%20that%20across%20three%20or%20four%20separate%20agencies%20with%20different%20processes%20sounds%20daunting%2C%20bureaucratic%2C%20and%20not%20particularly%20efficient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPotter%20says%20the%20funding%20whiplash%20and%20the%20gutting%20of%20the%20Education%20Department%20mean%20a%20rocky%20road%20ahead%20for%20students%20and%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20really%20challenging%20school%20year%2C%20and%20I%20think%20districts%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20they're%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20in%20terms%20of%20staffing%20and%20budgeting%20and%20how%20they%20make%20up%20for%20lost%20funds%2C%20is%20pretty%20unprecedented%2C%26quot%3B%20Potter%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStambaugh%20just%20wants%20clarity%20on%20what%20the%20Trump%20administration%20actually%20plans%20to%20do%20so%20she%20and%20other%20teachers%20can%20best%20prepare%20to%20help%20their%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20might%20actually%20be%20kind%20of%20in%20that%20flight%2C%20fight%2C%20or%20freeze%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we're%20all%20kind%20of%20frozen%2C%20waiting%20to%20see%20what's%20going%20to%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feducation-department-funding-staff-cuts-students-schools-student-loans-trump-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1760603761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c1844957d362d375e7e19b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feducation-department-funding-staff-cuts-students-schools-student-loans-trump-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22America's%20schools%20are%20facing%20a%20shaky%20start%20to%20the%20school%20year%20amid%20uncertainty%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Education.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feducation-department-funding-staff-cuts-students-schools-student-loans-trump-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20is%20Wanasah%20Kids%3F%20Meet%20the%20channel%20every%20parent%20in%20the%20Arab%20world%20wants%20on%20TV%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1760603703000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-124600013%2Cimgsize-1225820.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fwhat-is-wan